            <div class="heading-cta">
              <h2 class="no-margins">What is a Telecoil?</h2>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="story-text">
            <h4>
              A telecoil (or "T-coil") is a small copper wire loop embedded in
              many hearing aids and cochlear implants. It functions as an
              electromagnetic receiver, designed to detect signals from an
              assistive listening system.
            </h4>
            <div class="spacer-xs"></div>
            <h5>
              When enabled, the telecoil bypasses the device’s microphone and
              directly converts the magnetic field generated by the loop into
              audio signals. This allows for clearer, more focused sound by
              minimizing ambient noise and enhancing speech transmitted through
              microphones or public address systems.
            </h5>
            <div class="spacer-sm"></div>
            <div class="section-divider-light"></div>
            <div class="spacer-sm"></div>

            <div
